subject: RE: [junit] Announce: JDepend 1.4
msgSnippet: I did a quick once over on this code, and it doesn t look like that is the only thing.  The whole file-based scheme needs to be re-worked into the VAJ
messageBody:
I did a quick once over on this code, and it doesn't look like that is the
only thing. The whole file-based scheme needs to be re-worked into the VAJ
repository scheme. Unfortunately there is not a framework in the pulbic
space that makes these two schemes interchangeable (yet :) That should take
1 - 2 (full) weeks with testing. After that, the changes look to be minimal
and straight forward.

-Jason

> -----Original Message-----
> From: Michael Silverstein [mailto:msilverstein@...]
> Sent: Monday, July 23, 2001 1:57 PM
> To: junit@yahoogroups.com
> Subject: RE: [junit] Announce: JDepend 1.4
>
>
> If that's all, it's pretty trivial (i.e. no code
> required). You just need a
> file that describes the tools menu item names and the
> class to launch, like
> the one that JUnit uses in <va java install
> dir>\ide\tools\test-ui\default.ini:
>
> ----
> Name=JUnit
> Version=3.7
> Menu-Items=\
> JUnit,junit.ui.TestRunner, ;\
> JUnit,junit.ui.TestRunner,-c
> Quick-Start-Items=JUnit,junit.ui.TestRunner
> ----
>
> This installs a menu item in the main browser tools
> dropdown, and a menu
> item in the class browser tools popup.
> The -c means to pass the name of the class as an argument to the
> main(String[]) for the given class. Other options are -p
> for package, -P for
> project, etc.
>
> Mike

> > > > > > -----Original Message-----
> > > > > > From: Mike Clark [mailto:mike@...]
> > > > > > Sent: Friday, July 20, 2001 6:18 PM
> > > > > > To: junit@yahoogroups.com
> > > > > > Subject: [junit] Announce: JDepend 1.4
> > > > > >
> > > > > >
> > > > > > JDepend 1.4, the freely-available Java
> package dependency
> > > > > > analyzer, has
> > > > > > been released. Of particular interest to
> JUnit users is
> > > > > > the ability to
> > > > > > write tests that automatically check
> metrics tolerances,
> > > > > > existence of
> > > > > > package dependency cycles, and package dependency
> > > constraints.
> > > > > >
> > > > > >
> > > > > > New Features:
> > > > > >
> > > > > > - Added package dependency constraints to
> support writing
> > > > > > tests that
> > > > > > fail if any package dependency other than
> those declared in
> > > the
> > > > > > dependency constraints are detected. Refer to the
> > > > > > documentation or the
> > > > > > jdepend.framework.ConstraintTest class for complete
> > > examples.
> > > > > >
> > > > > > For example, the following test case
> method will fail
> > > > > > if the analyzed
> > > > > > packages contain any dependencies other
> than those declared
> > > in
> > > > > the
> > > > > > dependency constraint:
> > > > > >
> > > > > > public void testDependencyConstraint() {
> > > > > >
> > > > > > JavaPackage ejb = new
> JavaPackage("com.xyz.ejb");
> > > > > > JavaPackage web = new
> JavaPackage("com.xyz.web");
> > > > > > JavaPackage util = new
> JavaPackage("com.xyz.util");
> > > > > >
> > > > > > ejb.dependsUpon(util);
> > > > > > web.dependsUpon(util);
> > > > > >
> > > > > > DependencyConstraint constraint = new
> > > > > > DependencyConstraint();
> > > > > > constraint.addPackage(ejb);
> > > > > > constraint.addPackage(web);
> > > > > > constraint.addPackage(util);
> > > > > >
> > > > > > _jdepend.analyze();
> > > > > >
> > > > > >
> assert(_jdepend.dependencyMatch(constraint));
> > > > > > }
> > > > > >
> > > > > > - Added the jdepend.xmlui.JDepend class to generate
> > > > > > package metrics,
> > > > > > dependencies, and cycles in an XML format for easier
> > > > > > integration with
> > > > > > other tools.
> > > > > >
> > > > > > Example usage:
> > > > > > java jdepend.xmlui.JDepend -file report.xml
> > > > > /myproject/src
> > > > > >
> > > > > >
> > > > > > The JDepend documentation is available at
> > > > > >
> > > > > >
> http://www.clarkware.com/software/JDepend.html
> > > > > >
> > > > > > JDepend 1.4 can be downloaded directly from
> > > > > >
> > > > > >
> http://www.clarkware.com/software/jdepend1.4.zip
> > > > > >
> > > > > >
> > > > > > Any feedback you may have is most welcome
> and appreciated.
> > > > > >
> > > > > > Thanks and enjoy!
> > > > > >
> > > > > > Mike
